===============================================================================
[119] Persistenz auf UNIX-Datei Ebene
      12-Mar-1991 / Andreas Miethsam (UPA)

Ich habe etliche Module geaendert und zurueckgespielt, die es
ermoeglichen, auch interaktive CB Sitzungen und insbesondere
Untell Operationen abzuspeichern.
Dazu ist in GlobalParameters ein neues Fakt UpdateMode/1 mit
'persistent' zu belegen. Voreinstellung: 'nonpersistent'.

Der Umgang mit CB Applikationsfiles hat sich wie folgt geaendert:

Ab sofort besteht eine App. 'ExampleApp' nur noch aus je einem  File

    ExampleApp.prop              (Alle zur App. gehoerige Propositionen)

und optional je einem File

    ExampleApp.rule              (Regeln, Queries, IC,s)
    ExampleApp.builtin           (BuiltinQueries)
    ExampleApp_timeRel.pro       (Zeitbeziehungen)
    ExampleApp.hprop             (Historische Propositionen)

Damit die alten Appplikationen weiterhin laufen, muessen alle zu einer
App. gehoerigen .prop Files zu einem einzigen zusammenkopiert werden,
gleiches gilt fuer die .rule und _timeRel.pro Files.
Vorsicht: Diejenigen .rule Files, die BuiltinQueries enthalten, muessen
gesondert in ein File mit der Extension .builtin kopiert werden.

Beispiel (Annahme, alle .prop (.rule) Files in der aktuellen Directory
gehoeren zur Employee-App., waren bisher in Employee.app aufgezaehlt.):

% cat *.prop > Employee.copy
% mv Employee.copy Employee.prop
% cat *.rule > Employee.copy             # ohne Builtins !!!
% mv Employee.copy Employee.rule
% cat *_timeRel.pro > Employee.copy
% mv Employee.copy Employee_timeRel.pro
% rm Employee.copy

Das Laden einer App. geschieht wie bisher ueber den Button
'load application' im 'Models'-Menue bzw. ueber den Aufruf der Methode
'LOAD_APPLICATION' ueber eine der Programmierschnittstellen.
Naeheres zu der Wirkung von 'load application' (und auch 'add models' )
findet sich im 'ConceptBase V3.0 UserManual', Kap3 unter den entspr.
Methoden, sowie Kap4 u. Kap5 unter den entspr. Menuepunkten bei der
Benutzerfuehrung.


Es folgen Implementierungsdetails:

************************************************************************
Changed modules:
************************************************************************

*** Modules changed:

startCBserver.pro
LTassertionTranslator.pro
PROLOGruleProcessor.pro
MVS_start.pro
ModelConfiguration.pro
CBserverInterface.pro
GlobalParameters.pro
sTR.pro
ObjectProcessor.pro
BDMCompile.pro
ModelLoader.pro
BDMIntegrityChecker.pro
BDMKBMS.pro
TimeProcessor.pro
stopCBserver.pro
ConfigurationUtilities.pro

ModelLoader.pro
mvs_start.pro

*** Modules added:

WeakPersistency.pro


In more detail:

CBserver:

# BDMIntegrityChecker.pro
        mk_permanent_BDMFormulas now has arity 2. The new argument
        indicates whether a tell or untell operation caused the call
        of predicate mk_permanent_BDMFormulas.

# BDMCompile.pro
        some necessary asserts and retracts combined under the
        predicate name tell_ICcheck_functors called by remove_models
        from ModelConfiguration.

# BDMKBMS.pro
        predicate mk_permanent_BDMFormula now has arity 2 differing
        between the tell and untell case

#  CBserverInterface.pro
        new Method LOAD_APPLICATION defined

# ConfigurationUtilities.pro
        changed: load_prop; now loading history props too
        changed: load_sfg; some predicate calls removed, now done by
                                tell_objproc
        changed: process_list_of_SMLfragments; some predicate calls removed,
                                                now done by tell_objproc
        changed: system_create; taking into account that .prop files might
                                contain history props as well
        new: system_create_h; creating history propositions
        new: history_prop; separating history propositions from
                                actual propositions.
        removed: save_prop, save_list_of_prop, process_list_of_propval,
                process_list_of_clauses, process_list_of_timeRel;
                        now defined in WeakPersistency



# GlobalParameters.pro:
        2 new facts: UpdateMode/1, SystemApplication/2

        'UpdateMode' controls the way interactive updates of the current
        KB are treated.

        Possible settings:

        nonpersistent: updates will not be stored

        persistent : all facts, rules, Ic's, time relations resulting

                 from TELL/UNTELL operations will be stored

        'SystemApplication' contains the directory and the name where
        the system classes can be found.

# LTassertionTranslator.pro
        changed: closeRuleTTime; Transaction time of rules only temporaray
                closed.

# ModelConfiguration.pro
        changed: load_model; since the persistency change only .sfg and .sml
                files are considered.
        changed: load_application; resetting applications and loading of files
                .prop, .hprop, .rule, _timeRel.pro (when they exist).
        changed: loadSystemClasses; adapted for persistency
        changed: remove_models; adapted for persistency
        changed: load_result; setting search space in the prop case
        changed: clear_knowledgebase; brought up to date, now clearing the
                whole KB
        new: set_application; setting an application
        new: reset_application; setting an application, removing the old
                        application.
        new: get_application; retrieving the current application.
        new: CurrentApplication; fact containing the path and the name of
                        the current application.
        new: notify_change, set_nochange, changedKB; notifying when changes
                                to the KB occurred.


# ObjectProcessor.pro
        import SAVE/2 from WeakPersistency
        import UpdateMode/1 from GlobalParameters

        tell_objproc(...):-
        .
        .
        .
        ((UpdateMode(persistent),
          time( SAVE(generatedcode(_listofpropvals,_listofclauses,
                          _listoftimeRels), tell), _T1)                 {AM}
         );
          true
         ), ...

        The most important changes concern the predicates tell_objproc/
        untell_objproc. In both cases the changes to the KB will be made
        persistent (stored to the current application files) if 'UpdateMode'
        is set persistent.

# PROLOGruleProcessor.pro
        changed: delete_PROLOGrules; now all clauses are deleted from the
                current KB including clauses from the integrity checker.
        changed: store_toFile_PROLOGrules; file now opened with mode append
                (overwrite before).
        new: delete_fromFile_PROLOGrules; supporting UNtell.


# TimeProcessor.pro
        changed: store_toFile_timeRel: file now opened with mode append
                (overwrite before).
        new: delete_TimeRelations, needed for correct remove_models.

# startCBserver.pro
        loadSystemClasses removed, now imported from ModelConfiguration;
        additinally consulting new module WeakPersistency.pro;

# sTR.pro
        new: AbolishClusters  for abolishing time clusters, needed for
        correct remove_models.

# WeakPersistency.pro (new module)
        predicate: SAVE; main predicate for persistent savings, called by
                        tell_objproc and untell_objproc
        predicate: create_frame_from_propositions; stores Telos frames from
           all individuals retrievable from the current KB onto external file.
        predicate: create_backup_files; creates backup files of the files
               of the current application.
        predicate: cleanup;   removes some unnecessary facts from the files
               of the current application.
        predicate: process_list_of_clauses   *
        predicate: process_list_of_timeRel   *
        predicate: process_list_of_propval   *
        predicate: save_prop, save_list_of_prop   *
        predicate: save_list_of_prop   *

        (*) indicates predicates formerly defined in
            ConfigurationUtilities.pro.




CBinterface:

# ModelLoader.pro
        changed: load_application; now directly calling the respective method
                        of the CBserver

# mvs_start.pro
        changed: menu_system_create; 'load models' renamed to 'add models'
                [in menu choice 'editing' 'cml' renamed to 'Telos Frame'
                and 'argument' removed, but this has nothing to do with
                persistency.].


*** Some Problems:

- Extracting Telos frames from an existing .prop file is not yet implemented.
  Current version extracts only the individuals onto a file (by Prolog call).

- Inconsistent updates possible whenever 2 servers are working on the same
  application.

- Changing the SystemApplication may lead to inconsistencies to other
  (= user defined app's). This could be solved by copying the actual
  SystemApplication to an application at its creation time.

- Untelling time relations is not yet implemented.

- Currently there is only a 2 level backup mechanism of application files.
  SCCS would be an apropriate tool for this differential update task.

*** General comment:
  Applications should be known by the server, e.g. they should be
  instances of a class Application. Only the known (user accessible) app.
  should be loadable. Loading app's as an 'applicable decision'.


